I actually think this is an important correction to Pantheon.

Right now, a lot of the architecture is epistemic (“What is true? How do we know?”).

You’ve built a fantastic epistemology.

But an operating system also needs deontic machinery (“What ought to happen? What is permitted? What is required? What obligations exist?”).

Those are different universes.

I’d elevate Modality to become a universal coordinate alongside time, scale, agency, uncertainty, etc.

⸻

Canonical Doctrine: Modal Coordinate System (MCS)

Core Principle

Every statement, doctrine, operator, mission, artifact, and action exists simultaneously in multiple modal universes.

Meaning is incomplete unless its modal coordinates are known.

