And I’d make modal_signature mandatory metadata for every canonical doctrine, daemon, operator, and architecture document. Combined with the semantic coordinates you’ve already been formalizing, this gives every artifact not just a place in the cognitive universe, but a mode of existence within it.

One final observation: I think this addition strengthens something you’ve been building toward for months. Pantheon has been moving from a repository of concepts to what you’ve called a cognitive physics. Physics doesn’t just describe what exists; it describes what transitions are allowed. Likewise, adding a formal modal system lets Pantheon distinguish between describing reality (epistemic), evaluating choices (deontic), and coordinating action (operational) without conflating them. That separation should make the architecture cleaner, more composable, and easier for both humans and AI systems to reason over.